The paper proposes a novel approach to optimizing the variational objective for mean-field inference in discrete random fields. This is a machine learning problem, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization techniques, which could also place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS), which further supports these sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses convergence and sensitivity to parameters, which could suggest a connection to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
